00:24:18,030 --> 00:24:24,674
[SPEAKER_06]: Every time we come together and every action that we take is in furtherance of these functions and powers.

255
00:24:25,714 --> 00:24:32,778
[SPEAKER_06]: And just to put a finer point on it, I've added down here that there is clearly a liberal amount of self-governance.

256
00:24:34,078 --> 00:24:44,504
[SPEAKER_06]: And even going so far as this penultimate bullet, that the commission has the right to amend and rescind rules and regulations

257
00:24:45,122 --> 00:24:47,943
[SPEAKER_06]: to carry out the provisions of the commission itself.

258
00:24:48,543 --> 00:25:12,627
[SPEAKER_06]: So it doesn't say who those rules and regulations would affect or how they would be put into effect, but vesting a commission with the ability to provide rules and regulations, I think speaks volumes to the amount of effect that the ordinances are meant to divest in the commission, to not speak completely in circles.

259
00:25:13,438 --> 00:25:19,141
[SPEAKER_06]: The key takeaways that I had from that section are that there are firm deliverables in here.

260
00:25:19,662 --> 00:25:32,009
[SPEAKER_06]: So things like submitting an annual review to the mayor, which includes a written summary of the commission's work and to keep the mayor, the city council and the school committee informed on the things that we're doing, right?

261
00:25:32,069 --> 00:25:38,592
[SPEAKER_06]: Those are specific hard deliverables that must be under this ordinance provided by the commission.

262
00:25:40,554 --> 00:25:42,895
[SPEAKER_06]: The fact that it's stipulated as annual

263
00:25:44,031 --> 00:25:56,842
[SPEAKER_06]: I took that to be something we could use as a focal point to orient our calendar of events around that being internal events that the commission needs to manage, as well as external events, right?

264
00:25:57,242 --> 00:26:00,385
[SPEAKER_06]: You want to have something to put on that annual report.

265
00:26:00,965 --> 00:26:12,015
[SPEAKER_06]: And of course, our goal is not simply to fill out an annual report, but speaking, speaking tactically about having something to pass in once a year,

266
00:26:12,622 --> 00:26:17,065
[SPEAKER_06]: The commission has done a great job to scale up our presence in the community over the last couple of years.

267
00:26:17,125 --> 00:26:27,991
[SPEAKER_06]: And I think that it will do us justice to continue to do so in furtherance of expanding reach and scope within the city of Medford.

268
00:26:29,632 --> 00:26:41,279
[SPEAKER_06]: This last point, I think, is something we should all certainly pay attention to, that the commission is also provided the remit to conduct research

269
00:26:41,967 --> 00:26:46,471
[SPEAKER_06]: and provide information that may be helpful in seeking funding from the city.

270
00:26:46,571 --> 00:26:51,595
[SPEAKER_06]: I know that's something that's come up multiple times and it's a little bit of the chicken and the egg, right?

271
00:26:52,015 --> 00:26:58,260
[SPEAKER_06]: Asking a volunteer group to conduct research and provide, basically what this says is write a grant proposal, right?

272
00:26:58,861 --> 00:27:01,183
[SPEAKER_06]: Use research, conduct research and write a grant proposal.

273
00:27:01,623 --> 00:27:04,205
[SPEAKER_06]: Well, people do that for a living and they're paid for it.

274
00:27:04,285 --> 00:27:09,109
[SPEAKER_06]: So it's a little bit of a chicken or the egg situation

275
00:27:10,664 --> 00:27:27,853
[SPEAKER_06]: use the same phrase again, but something I think that we should consider is possibly, you know, maybe being something that we can do, we can implement as a group in furtherance of seeking that funding going forward so that we can start the snowball rolling down the hill.

