00:28:02,097 --> 00:28:03,318
[SPEAKER_06]: I wasn't going to copy and paste.

283
00:28:04,379 --> 00:28:09,181
[SPEAKER_06]: But a few items of note that I saw in the definitions were that

284
00:28:11,827 --> 00:28:18,631
[SPEAKER_06]: The current illegal use of a controlled substance as defined by the Massachusetts general laws is listed as a disability.

285
00:28:18,651 --> 00:28:27,336
[SPEAKER_06]: I don't have anything to add to that other than I thought that it was something that should be raised given the remit of the commission.

286
00:28:30,158 --> 00:28:39,363
[SPEAKER_06]: The fact that again, the definition of discriminate does include outcomes that are both by design and by effect.

287
00:28:39,977 --> 00:28:53,122
[SPEAKER_06]: So it doesn't need to be that something was clearly implemented with the intent to disenfranchise or discriminate that only in those cases, the HRC can take corrective action.

288
00:28:53,262 --> 00:29:03,946
[SPEAKER_06]: It can be if there are policies and procedures or other items that have in effect discriminated against folks that the HRC can take action.

289
00:29:04,626 --> 00:29:09,408
[SPEAKER_06]: And there was a specific definition provided as to human rights

290
00:29:10,702 --> 00:29:19,644
[SPEAKER_06]: that I think is worth highlighting because again, what you see here is extremely broad, which I think for us is very helpful.

291
00:29:20,124 --> 00:29:23,845
[SPEAKER_06]: We want to have the widest breadth and depth of effect that we can.

292
00:29:24,445 --> 00:29:30,446
[SPEAKER_06]: The fact that this definition is so vast in scope is helpful.

293
00:29:30,946 --> 00:29:38,368
[SPEAKER_06]: Again, it refers back to the Constitution of the US and the Constitution of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, reinforcing those as final backstops.

294
00:29:40,232 --> 00:29:41,573
[SPEAKER_06]: The last few topics for discussion.

295
00:29:41,593 --> 00:29:44,794
[SPEAKER_06]: And I don't want to monopolize all the time.

296
00:29:44,834 --> 00:29:45,855
[SPEAKER_06]: Hopefully I've gone through this.

297
00:29:46,475 --> 00:29:51,297
[SPEAKER_06]: In such a manner that is not too fast to understand and not too slow.

298
00:29:51,337 --> 00:29:55,740
[SPEAKER_06]: So as to lose your attention, but the last few topics for discussion that I took out of this.

299
00:29:57,120 --> 00:30:01,842
[SPEAKER_06]: We're potentially the content here can be used as a rubric for the commission to organize itself.

300
00:30:09,600 --> 00:30:12,001
[SPEAKER_06]: evidence of the work that we're doing in the community.

