00:31:40,230 --> 00:31:42,850
[SPEAKER_06]: And personally, I do think it's important as well.

314
00:31:42,910 --> 00:31:44,131
[SPEAKER_06]: So I'll hand things off to you.

315
00:31:45,571 --> 00:31:45,911
[SPEAKER_03]: Sure.

316
00:31:46,071 --> 00:31:59,775
[SPEAKER_03]: And then the ordinance makes it crystal clear that part of the role of the commission is to be available to listen to Medford residents if they have a grievance and it speaks to

317
00:32:01,630 --> 00:32:07,191
[SPEAKER_03]: what Chief Buckley brought up, I think the last meeting, saying he thought it was baked in.

318
00:32:07,911 --> 00:32:15,753
[SPEAKER_03]: And then when I started doing my research on human rights commissions, I think I looked at five or six communities.

319
00:32:16,453 --> 00:32:29,515
[SPEAKER_03]: It is standard operating procedure that all of the commissioners on those missions listen to grievances if anyone in the city, you know,

320
00:32:30,739 --> 00:32:35,603
[SPEAKER_03]: needs to file a formal complaint or whatever.

321
00:32:35,843 --> 00:32:56,960
[SPEAKER_03]: So given that is standard operating procedure across many or if not all human rights commissions, and I did hear in past meetings, there was some concern about our capacity to be able to handle those and questioning whether we should do that.

322
00:32:57,661 --> 00:32:59,002
[SPEAKER_03]: You know, my question is,

323
00:32:59,657 --> 00:33:04,918
[SPEAKER_03]: can the city offer some sort of training on dispute resolution?

324
00:33:04,958 --> 00:33:19,281
[SPEAKER_03]: And I know from the line of work that I do, community building, I rely heavily on like leaders and committees whenever an alum, I do alumni relations.

325
00:33:20,041 --> 00:33:28,063
[SPEAKER_03]: If we're having a complication or a challenge or a complaint, I will usually have another alum help us in terms of being

326
00:33:28,730 --> 00:33:34,235
[SPEAKER_03]: an empathetic listener and an active listener to be able to help us sort out.

327
00:33:34,655 --> 00:33:38,219
[SPEAKER_03]: So I think that that's something we should also carefully think about.

