00:52:32,804 --> 00:52:34,185
[SPEAKER_04]: No, no, I was just going to say, I think

491
00:52:36,205 --> 00:52:39,569
[SPEAKER_04]: I wanna, I'm wanting to feel cognizant of the difference between

492
00:52:41,223 --> 00:52:51,928
[SPEAKER_04]: a communication mechanism feeling like a peer support slash mentorship kind of piece where like, yes, I think we are all moving from a place of compassion.

493
00:52:51,948 --> 00:52:58,431
[SPEAKER_04]: I think we want to see Medford pursue conversations around restorative justice, et cetera, et cetera.

494
00:52:58,451 --> 00:53:04,955
[SPEAKER_04]: But that doesn't feel like the same as being trained in empirical and sort of evidence-based conflict resolution techniques.

495
00:53:05,395 --> 00:53:09,577
